div.p:
Zero Overhead Guarantee
In release builds, the preprocessor completely removes all debug code before the compiler sees it. The generated binary has no branches, no poison checks, and no canary operations.
This is fundamentally different from runtime flags:
c
// WRONG: Runtime check (overhead remains)
if (pool->debug_mode) { check_poison(); }
// RIGHT: Compile-time (zero overhead)
#ifdef POOL_DEBUG
check_poison();
#endif
